search:react-native-firebase-authenticat.content:
- Use `npx react-native init MyProject` to create a new React Native project.
- Install Firebase SDK using `npm install --save @react-native-firebase/app @react-native-firebase/auth`.
- For the latest versions, check [Firebase documentation](https://firebase.google.com/docs).
- Key config options include:
  - `apiKey`: Your Firebase project's API key.
  - `authDomain`: The domain of your Firebase project.
  - `projectId`: Your Firebase project ID.
  - `storageBucket`: Your Firebase storage bucket name.
  - `messagingSenderId`: Your Firebase messaging sender ID.
  - `appId`: Your Firebase app ID.
- Implement email/password authentication with:
  ```javascript
  import auth from '@react-native-firebase/auth';

  const register = (email, password) => {
    auth()
      .createUserWithEmailAndPassword(email, password)
      .then(() => {
        // User registered successfully
      })
      .catch(error => {
        if (error.code === 'auth/email-already-in-use') {
          console.log('That email address is already in use!');
        }

        if (error.code === 'auth/invalid-email') {
          console.log('That email address is invalid!');
        }

        console.error(error);
      });
  };

  const login = (email, password) => {
    auth()
      .signInWithEmailAndPassword(email, password)
      .then(() => {
        // User logged in successfully
      })
      .catch(error => {
        if (error.code === 'auth/user-not-found') {
          console.log('That email address is not registered!');
        }

        if (error.code === 'auth/wrong-password') {
          console.log('Wrong password, please try again.');
        }

        console.error(error);
      });
  };
  ```
- For social logins, use `signInWithCredential` with the appropriate provider credentials.
- Implement account linking by using `fetchSignInMethodsForEmail` and `linkWithCredential`.
- Ensure security by enabling email verification and implementing password policies.
